## 2. Entry Points — Where Data Enters the System

Data enters PakEscrow through **four primary entry points**:

| # | Entry Point | Who Sends It | Data Sent |
|---|---|---|---|
| 1 | **Registration Form** | Freelancer or Client | Name, email, phone, role, password |
| 2 | **KYC Upload Portal** | Registered user | CNIC images, selfie, proof of address |
| 3 | **Contract Creation Form** | Client | Project title, scope, amount, deadline, terms |
| 4 | **Payment Gateway Webhook** | JazzCash / EasyPaisa / HBL | Payment confirmation, gateway reference, amount |

Additionally, two **system-internal entry points** generate data automatically:

| # | Internal Source | What It Writes |
|---|---|---|
| 5 | **Application Event Bus** | Audit log entries on every state change |
| 6 | **Notification Worker (BullMQ)** | Notification records dispatched to email/SMS/in-app |

