## 3. Flow 1 — User Registration & Identity

**Trigger:** A freelancer or client submits the registration form.

### Step-by-Step Data Movement

```
Step 1 — Form submission arrives at POST /api/v1/auth/register
         │
         ▼
Step 2 — Input validated (email format, phone format, password strength)
         │
         ▼
Step 3 — WRITE to [ users ]
         │  New row created with:
         │  • id          = system-generated UUID
         │  • email       = from form
         │  • phone       = from form (Pakistani format +923XXXXXXXXX)
         │  • role        = FREELANCER or CLIENT
         │  • kyc_tier    = 1 (default — phone+email only)
         │  • is_active   = TRUE
         │  • profile_data = JSON (name, city, skills if freelancer)
         │  • created_at  = current timestamp
         │
         ▼
Step 4 — WRITE to [ wallets ]   ← depends on users.id
         │  One wallet auto-created per user:
         │  • user_id         = users.id (FK)
         │  • balance         = 0.0000
         │  • locked_balance  = 0.0000
         │  • currency        = PKR
         │  • is_frozen       = FALSE
         │
         ▼
Step 5 — WRITE to [ audit_logs ]  ← triggered automatically
         │  Action: USER_REGISTERED
         │  actor_id = new users.id
         │  entity_type = 'user'
         │  before_snapshot = {}
         │  after_snapshot  = {email, role}
         │
         ▼
Step 6 — WRITE to [ notifications ]
         │  Event: WELCOME_EMAIL
         │  Channel: EMAIL + SMS
         │  Payload: Welcome message with OTP verification link
         │
         ▼
Step 7 — OUTPUT: JWT access token + refresh token returned to client
```

### Tables Written

| Table | Operation | Data Written |
|---|---|---|
| `users` | INSERT | Complete user profile row |
| `wallets` | INSERT | Zero-balance wallet linked to new user |
| `audit_logs` | INSERT | USER_REGISTERED event |
| `notifications` | INSERT | Welcome + OTP verification message |

### Tables Read (Validation)

| Table | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `users` | Check email uniqueness before insert |
| `users` | Check phone uniqueness before insert |

### Dependencies

```
users           ← no dependencies (root table, created first)
wallets         ← depends on users.id (must exist before wallet is created)
audit_logs      ← depends on users.id (actor_id FK)
notifications   ← depends on users.id (user_id FK)
```

