## 4. Flow 2 — KYC Verification

**Trigger:** A registered user submits identity documents to unlock higher transaction limits.

### Step-by-Step Data Movement

```
Step 1 — User uploads CNIC front, CNIC back, and selfie
         via POST /api/v1/kyc/submit (multipart form)
         │
         ▼
Step 2 — Files uploaded to AWS S3 (private bucket)
         │  Each file stored at: kyc/{user_id}/{doc_type}_{uuid}.jpg
         │  S3 key returned to application
         │
         ▼
Step 3 — WRITE to [ kyc_documents ]  ← depends on users.id
         │  One row per document uploaded:
         │  • user_id       = submitting user's UUID (FK → users)
         │  • document_type = CNIC_FRONT | CNIC_BACK | SELFIE | PROOF_OF_ADDRESS
         │  • file_s3_key   = S3 storage path (not the file itself)
         │  • status        = PENDING
         │  • reviewed_by   = NULL (not yet reviewed)
         │  • reviewed_at   = NULL
         │
         ▼
Step 4 — WRITE to [ audit_logs ]
         │  Action: KYC_SUBMITTED
         │  actor_id = submitting user
         │
         ▼
Step 5 — WRITE to [ notifications ]
         │  Event: KYC_SUBMITTED_CONFIRMATION
         │  Channel: EMAIL
         │
         ▼
Step 6 — Admin opens KYC review queue in dashboard
         READ from [ kyc_documents ] WHERE status = 'PENDING'
         READ from [ users ] to fetch submitter profile
         │
         ▼
Step 7 — Admin approves or rejects
         │
         ▼
Step 8 — UPDATE [ kyc_documents ]
         │  • status      = APPROVED | REJECTED
         │  • reviewed_by = admin's users.id (FK → users)
         │  • reviewed_at = current timestamp
         │
         ▼
Step 9 — UPDATE [ users ]
         │  • kyc_tier = 2 or 3 (based on documents approved)
         │
         ▼
Step 10 — WRITE to [ audit_logs ]
          Action: KYC_APPROVED or KYC_REJECTED
          actor_id = admin user
          before_snapshot = {status: 'PENDING'}
          after_snapshot  = {status: 'APPROVED', reviewed_by: admin_id}
          │
          ▼
Step 11 — WRITE to [ notifications ]
          Event: KYC_APPROVED or KYC_REJECTED
          Channel: EMAIL + SMS
          │
          ▼
Step 12 — OUTPUT: User's transaction limit unlocked (reflected in users.kyc_tier)
```

### Tables Written

| Table | Operation | Trigger |
|---|---|---|
| `kyc_documents` | INSERT | User submits documents |
| `kyc_documents` | UPDATE | Admin reviews and decides |
| `users` | UPDATE | kyc_tier upgraded after approval |
| `audit_logs` | INSERT | On submit and on review decision |
| `notifications` | INSERT | On submit confirmation and review result |

### Dependencies

```
kyc_documents   ← depends on users.id (user_id FK)
kyc_documents   ← depends on users.id (reviewed_by FK — admin)
audit_logs      ← depends on users.id (actor_id FK)
notifications   ← depends on users.id (user_id FK)
```

