## 5. Flow 3 — Contract Creation & Acceptance

**Trigger:** A client creates an escrow contract and a freelancer accepts it.

### Step-by-Step Data Movement

```
Step 1 — Client fills contract form: title, scope, amount, deadline, terms
         POST /api/v1/escrow
         │
         ▼
Step 2 — System validates:
         READ [ users ] to confirm client's kyc_tier allows contract amount
         READ [ users ] to confirm freelancer_id exists
         READ [ wallets ] to confirm client has sufficient balance (not required
         at creation — payment comes later, but limit checks apply)
         │
         ▼
Step 3 — WRITE to [ contracts ]
         │  • id                = new UUID
         │  • reference_number  = PKE-2024-XXXXX (sequential, unique)
         │  • client_id         = requesting user's UUID (FK → users)
         │  • freelancer_id     = invited freelancer's UUID (FK → users)
         │  • title             = from form
         │  • scope             = from form
         │  • total_amount      = from form (NUMERIC 20,4)
         │  • platform_fee      = total_amount × 1.5% (calculated at creation)
         │  • currency          = PKR
         │  • status            = DRAFT
         │  • terms             = JSONB (file formats, revision policy, etc.)
         │  • max_revisions     = from form (default 3)
         │  • revision_count    = 0
         │  • delivery_deadline = from form
         │  • created_at        = now()
         │
         ▼
Step 4 — WRITE to [ milestones ]  ← if milestone-based contract
         │  One row per milestone:
         │  • contract_id = contracts.id (FK)
         │  • title, description, amount, sequence, due_date
         │  • status = PENDING
         │
         ▼
Step 5 — WRITE to [ notifications ]
         │  Event: CONTRACT_INVITATION
         │  Recipient: freelancer
         │  Channel: EMAIL + SMS
         │  Payload: Contract title, amount, deadline, accept link
         │
         ▼
Step 6 — WRITE to [ audit_logs ]
         │  Action: CONTRACT_CREATED
         │  actor_id = client user
         │
         ▼
Step 7 — Freelancer reviews and accepts
         POST /api/v1/escrow/:id/accept
         │
         ▼
Step 8 — UPDATE [ contracts ]
         │  • status = PENDING_ACCEPTANCE → accepted state
         │  • updated_at = now()
         │
         ▼
Step 9 — WRITE to [ notifications ]
         │  Event: CONTRACT_ACCEPTED
         │  Recipient: client
         │  Channel: EMAIL + IN_APP
         │
         ▼
Step 10 — WRITE to [ audit_logs ]
          Action: CONTRACT_ACCEPTED
          actor_id = freelancer user
          │
          ▼
Step 11 — OUTPUT: Contract visible on both dashboards
          Status: PENDING_ACCEPTANCE (awaiting client payment)
```

### Tables Written

| Table | Operation | Trigger |
|---|---|---|
| `contracts` | INSERT | Client submits contract form |
| `contracts` | UPDATE | Freelancer accepts |
| `milestones` | INSERT | If milestone-based — one row per phase |
| `audit_logs` | INSERT | On creation and on acceptance |
| `notifications` | INSERT | Invitation to freelancer; confirmation to client |

### Dependencies

```
contracts     ← depends on users.id × 2 (client_id FK, freelancer_id FK)
milestones    ← depends on contracts.id (contract_id FK)
audit_logs    ← depends on users.id (actor_id FK)
notifications ← depends on users.id (user_id FK)
```

