## 6. Flow 4 — Escrow Funding (Payment In)

**Trigger:** Client deposits the contract amount via a payment gateway.

### Step-by-Step Data Movement

```
Step 1 — Client selects payment gateway (JazzCash / EasyPaisa / HBL / Bank)
         POST /api/v1/escrow/:id/fund
         │
         ▼
Step 2 — Platform redirects client to gateway payment page
         No database write yet — payment is pending
         │
         ▼
Step 3 — Client completes payment on gateway
         Gateway sends HMAC-signed webhook to:
         POST /api/v1/webhooks/jazzcash  (or easypaisa / hbl)
         │
         ▼
Step 4 — HMAC signature validated (webhook rejected if invalid)
         │
         ▼
Step 5 — WRITE to [ payments ]  ← depends on contracts.id and users.id
         │  • id           = new UUID
         │  • contract_id  = contracts.id (FK)
         │  • user_id      = client's users.id (FK)
         │  • amount       = contract total_amount (NUMERIC 20,4)
         │  • gateway      = JAZZCASH | EASYPAISA | HBL | BANK_TRANSFER
         │  • gateway_ref  = gateway's own transaction reference
         │  • status       = SUCCESS
         │  • direction    = DEPOSIT
         │  • created_at   = now()
         │
         ▼
Step 6 — UPDATE [ wallets ] — client wallet  ← within same DB transaction
         │  BEGIN TRANSACTION
         │  SELECT ... FOR UPDATE ON wallets WHERE user_id = client_id
         │  (pessimistic row-level lock — prevents double-spend)
         │  • locked_balance = locked_balance + contract.total_amount
         │  • updated_at    = now()
         │  COMMIT
         │
         ▼
Step 7 — UPDATE [ contracts ]
         │  • status    = FUNDED
         │  • funded_at = now()
         │  • updated_at = now()
         │
         ▼
Step 8 — UPDATE [ milestones ] (if milestone contract)
         │  First milestone: status = IN_PROGRESS, funded_at = now()
         │
         ▼
Step 9 — WRITE to [ audit_logs ]
         │  Action: CONTRACT_FUNDED
         │  actor_id = client
         │  before_snapshot = {status: 'PENDING_ACCEPTANCE'}
         │  after_snapshot  = {status: 'FUNDED', amount: X}
         │
         ▼
Step 10 — WRITE to [ notifications ]
          │  Event: CONTRACT_FUNDED
          │  Recipient 1: freelancer — "Funds secured. You may begin work."
          │  Recipient 2: client    — "Your payment has been locked in escrow."
          │  Channel: EMAIL + SMS
          │
          ▼
Step 11 — OUTPUT:
          • contracts.status = FUNDED
          • wallets.locked_balance increased by contract amount
          • Freelancer receives green light to begin work
```

### Tables Written

| Table | Operation | Trigger |
|---|---|---|
| `payments` | INSERT | Webhook confirms successful gateway payment |
| `wallets` | UPDATE | locked_balance increased (within DB transaction) |
| `contracts` | UPDATE | status → FUNDED, funded_at recorded |
| `milestones` | UPDATE | First milestone status → IN_PROGRESS |
| `audit_logs` | INSERT | CONTRACT_FUNDED event |
| `notifications` | INSERT | Both parties notified |

### Database Transaction Guarantee

```
BEGIN;
  -- Lock client wallet row
  SELECT * FROM wallets WHERE user_id = $client_id FOR UPDATE;

  -- Record payment
  INSERT INTO payments (...) VALUES (...);

  -- Lock funds
  UPDATE wallets SET locked_balance = locked_balance + $amount
  WHERE user_id = $client_id;

  -- Advance contract state
  UPDATE contracts SET status = 'FUNDED', funded_at = NOW()
  WHERE id = $contract_id;

COMMIT;
-- If any step fails → entire block rolls back. No partial state.
```

### Dependencies

```
payments    ← depends on contracts.id (contract_id FK)
payments    ← depends on users.id    (user_id FK)
wallets     ← depends on users.id    (user_id FK)
audit_logs  ← depends on users.id    (actor_id FK)
```

