## 7. Flow 5 — Milestone Management

**Trigger:** Freelancer completes a phase of work and delivers a milestone.

### Step-by-Step Data Movement

```
Step 1 — Freelancer submits milestone delivery
         POST /api/v1/escrow/:id/milestones/:milestoneId/deliver
         Body: { description, file_attachments[], external_links[] }
         │
         ▼
Step 2 — READ [ contracts ] to confirm status = IN_PROGRESS or FUNDED
         READ [ milestones ] to confirm milestone status = IN_PROGRESS
         READ [ users ] to confirm requester is the contract's freelancer
         │
         ▼
Step 3 — Delivery files uploaded to AWS S3
         S3 keys stored in milestone metadata
         │
         ▼
Step 4 — UPDATE [ milestones ]
         │  • status     = DELIVERED
         │  • updated_at = now()
         │
         ▼
Step 5 — UPDATE [ contracts ]
         │  • status     = DELIVERED (if final milestone)
         │  • updated_at = now()
         │
         ▼
Step 6 — WRITE to [ audit_logs ]
         │  Action: MILESTONE_DELIVERED
         │  actor_id = freelancer
         │
         ▼
Step 7 — WRITE to [ notifications ]
         │  Event: DELIVERY_SUBMITTED
         │  Recipient: client
         │  Channel: EMAIL + SMS + IN_APP
         │  Payload: "Review delivery within 3 days."
         │
         ▼
Step 8 — Client reviews and APPROVES milestone
         POST /api/v1/escrow/:id/milestones/:milestoneId/approve
         │
         ▼
Step 9 — READ [ wallets ] WHERE user_id = freelancer_id FOR UPDATE
         (lock freelancer wallet before credit)
         │
         ▼
Step 10 — UPDATE [ wallets ] — client wallet
          │  • locked_balance = locked_balance - milestone.amount
          │
          ▼
Step 11 — UPDATE [ wallets ] — freelancer wallet
          │  • balance = balance + (milestone.amount - proportional_fee)
          │
          ▼
Step 12 — UPDATE [ milestones ]
          │  • status      = APPROVED
          │  • released_at = now()
          │
          ▼
Step 13 — WRITE to [ payments ]
          │  • direction = RELEASE
          │  • amount    = milestone.amount - fee
          │  • user_id   = freelancer's UUID
          │
          ▼
Step 14 — UPDATE [ contracts ]
          │  If all milestones APPROVED: status = COMPLETED, completed_at = now()
          │  Otherwise: status remains IN_PROGRESS, next milestone activated
          │
          ▼
Step 15 — WRITE to [ audit_logs ]
          │  Action: MILESTONE_APPROVED
          │
          ▼
Step 16 — WRITE to [ notifications ]
          │  Event: MILESTONE_APPROVED
          │  Recipient: freelancer
          │  Channel: EMAIL + IN_APP
          │
          ▼
Step 17 — OUTPUT: Freelancer wallet balance increased
          Next milestone unlocked (if applicable)
          Contract completed (if final milestone)
```

### Revision Request Sub-Flow

```
Client rejects milestone → WRITE to [ contracts ]: revision_count + 1
If revision_count < max_revisions:
    UPDATE [ milestones ]: status = IN_PROGRESS (returned to freelancer)
    WRITE  [ notifications ]: REVISION_REQUESTED → freelancer
    WRITE  [ audit_logs ]: REVISION_REQUESTED
If revision_count >= max_revisions:
    Client offered option to raise a DISPUTE (→ Flow 7)
```

### Tables Written (Milestone Flow)

| Table | Operation | Trigger |
|---|---|---|
| `milestones` | UPDATE | Status: IN_PROGRESS → DELIVERED → APPROVED |
| `contracts` | UPDATE | Status advances; completed_at set if last milestone |
| `wallets` | UPDATE × 2 | Client locked_balance ↓ ; Freelancer balance ↑ |
| `payments` | INSERT | RELEASE direction record |
| `audit_logs` | INSERT | Per state transition |
| `notifications` | INSERT | Delivery alert + approval confirmation |

