## 8. Flow 6 — Delivery, Approval & Fund Release

**Trigger:** Single-payment contract delivered and approved by client.

### Step-by-Step Data Movement

```
Step 1 — Freelancer submits final delivery
         POST /api/v1/escrow/:id/deliver
         │
         ▼
Step 2 — UPDATE [ contracts ]
         │  • status = DELIVERED
         │
         ▼
Step 3 — WRITE to [ notifications ]
         │  Event: DELIVERY_SUBMITTED → client
         │  "Review within 3 days. Auto-escalation if no action."
         │
         ▼
Step 4 — CLIENT APPROVES delivery
         POST /api/v1/escrow/:id/approve
         │
         ▼
Step 5 — BEGIN TRANSACTION (atomic fund release)
         │
         ├─ Step 5a — READ [ wallets ] client row   FOR UPDATE (lock)
         ├─ Step 5b — READ [ wallets ] freelancer row FOR UPDATE (lock)
         ├─ Step 5c — READ [ contracts ] to verify status = DELIVERED
         │
         ├─ Step 5d — UPDATE [ wallets ] client
         │              locked_balance = locked_balance - total_amount
         │
         ├─ Step 5e — UPDATE [ wallets ] freelancer
         │              balance = balance + (total_amount - platform_fee)
         │
         ├─ Step 5f — WRITE to [ payments ]
         │              direction = RELEASE
         │              amount    = total_amount - platform_fee
         │              user_id   = freelancer UUID
         │              status    = SUCCESS
         │
         └─ Step 5g — UPDATE [ contracts ]
                        status       = COMPLETED
                        completed_at = now()
         │
         COMMIT
         │
         ▼
Step 6 — WRITE to [ audit_logs ]
         │  Action: CONTRACT_APPROVED + FUNDS_RELEASED
         │  Two log entries written sequentially with chain hashes
         │
         ▼
Step 7 — WRITE to [ notifications ]
         │  Recipient 1: client    — "Contract completed. Thank you."
         │  Recipient 2: freelancer — "PKR X released to your wallet."
         │  Channel: EMAIL + SMS + IN_APP
         │
         ▼
Step 8 — OUTPUT:
         • contracts.status = COMPLETED
         • Freelancer wallet balance = previous + net_amount
         • Client locked_balance = 0 for this contract
         • Platform fee retained in system escrow wallet
         • Both users can download transaction receipt
```

### Fund Flow Diagram

```
BEFORE APPROVAL:
  Client Wallet:     balance=50,000  locked_balance=30,000
  Freelancer Wallet: balance=5,000   locked_balance=0
  System Escrow:     holds 30,000

AFTER APPROVAL (contract amount = 30,000 | platform_fee = 450):
  Client Wallet:     balance=50,000  locked_balance=0
  Freelancer Wallet: balance=34,550  locked_balance=0  (+29,550 net)
  Platform Revenue:  +450 (fee retained)
```

