## 9. Flow 7 — Dispute Resolution

**Trigger:** Client or freelancer raises a formal dispute on an active contract.

### Step-by-Step Data Movement

```
Step 1 — User raises dispute
         POST /api/v1/disputes
         Body: { contract_id, reason, description }
         │
         ▼
Step 2 — READ [ contracts ] to verify:
         • status is IN_PROGRESS, DELIVERED, or FUNDED
         • requester is client_id or freelancer_id on that contract
         │
         ▼
Step 3 — WRITE to [ disputes ]
         │  • id           = new UUID
         │  • contract_id  = contracts.id (FK)
         │  • raised_by    = requesting user UUID (FK → users)
         │  • reason       = NON_DELIVERY | QUALITY_NOT_MET | SCOPE_DISAGREEMENT |
         │                   LATE_DELIVERY | PAYMENT_WITHHELD | OTHER
         │  • status       = RAISED
         │  • assigned_to  = NULL (not yet assigned)
         │  • created_at   = now()
         │
         ▼
Step 4 — UPDATE [ contracts ]
         │  • status = DISPUTED
         │  Funds remain LOCKED — neither party can access them
         │
         ▼
Step 5 — WRITE to [ audit_logs ]
         │  Action: DISPUTE_RAISED
         │
         ▼
Step 6 — WRITE to [ notifications ]
         │  Recipient 1: other party  — "A dispute has been raised. Submit evidence."
         │  Recipient 2: admin queue  — "New dispute requires assignment."
         │  Channel: EMAIL + SMS
         │
         ▼
Step 7 — Admin assigns moderator
         PATCH /api/v1/admin/disputes/:id/assign
         │
         ▼
Step 8 — UPDATE [ disputes ]
         │  • status      = UNDER_REVIEW
         │  • assigned_to = moderator's users.id (FK → users)
         │
         ▼
Step 9 — Both parties submit evidence
         POST /api/v1/disputes/:id/evidence
         Files uploaded to S3; references stored in disputes.terms (JSONB)
         │
         ▼
Step 10 — UPDATE [ disputes ]
          │  • status = EVIDENCE_SUBMITTED
          │
          ▼
Step 11 — Moderator reviews evidence and makes decision
          POST /api/v1/admin/disputes/:id/resolve
          Body: { resolution_type, resolution_note }
          │
          ▼
Step 12 — UPDATE [ disputes ]
          │  • status           = RESOLVED
          │  • resolution_type  = FULL_RELEASE | FULL_REFUND | PARTIAL_SPLIT
          │  • resolution_note  = moderator's written justification
          │  • resolved_at      = now()
          │
          ▼
Step 13 — Execute resolution (atomic DB transaction):
          │
          ├─ FULL_RELEASE:
          │    UPDATE wallets (client)     locked_balance - total_amount
          │    UPDATE wallets (freelancer) balance + (total_amount - fee)
          │    INSERT payments             direction=RELEASE
          │    UPDATE contracts            status=COMPLETED, completed_at=now()
          │
          ├─ FULL_REFUND:
          │    UPDATE wallets (client)     locked_balance - total_amount
          │    UPDATE wallets (client)     balance + total_amount
          │    INSERT payments             direction=REFUND
          │    UPDATE contracts            status=REFUNDED, cancelled_at=now()
          │
          └─ PARTIAL_SPLIT (e.g. 60% freelancer / 40% client):
               UPDATE wallets (freelancer) balance + split_freelancer_amount
               UPDATE wallets (client)     locked_balance - total_amount
               UPDATE wallets (client)     balance + split_client_amount
               INSERT payments × 2         RELEASE + REFUND records
               UPDATE contracts            status=COMPLETED
          │
          ▼
Step 14 — WRITE to [ audit_logs ]
          │  Action: DISPUTE_RESOLVED
          │  actor_id = moderator
          │  after_snapshot = {resolution_type, resolution_note}
          │
          ▼
Step 15 — WRITE to [ notifications ]
          │  Both parties notified of decision via EMAIL + SMS
          │
          ▼
Step 16 — OUTPUT:
          • Dispute closed with binding decision
          • Wallets updated per resolution
          • Both parties receive written decision
          • Full evidence trail preserved in audit_logs and disputes table
```

### Escalation Sub-Flow

```
If either party contests moderator decision:
  UPDATE [ disputes ] status = ESCALATED
  Assigned to COMPLIANCE_OFFICER (senior role)
  New audit_log entry: DISPUTE_ESCALATED
  New notification to both parties: case escalated
  Senior officer reviews → same resolution flow from Step 11
```

