## 11. Cross-Cutting Flows — Audit & Notifications

These two flows do not have a single trigger — they are written to **on every state change** across all other flows. They are the platform's memory and communication backbone.

### Audit Log Flow

```
Every state-changing API call:
  │
  ▼
Application intercept layer (NestJS interceptor)
  │  Captures: actor_id, action_name, entity_type, entity_id,
  │            before_state (snapshot before DB write),
  │            after_state  (snapshot after DB write),
  │            ip_address, user_agent
  │
  ▼
WRITE to [ audit_logs ]
  │  chain_hash = SHA-256(previous_log_hash + current_entry_content)
  │  This creates a tamper-evident chain:
  │  if any historical log entry is modified, the hash chain breaks
  │
  ▼
No further dependencies — audit_logs is a write-only append table
READ only by: admin dashboard, compliance export, legal discovery
```

### Notification Flow

```
Every domain event emitted by a service:
  ContractFunded | DeliverySubmitted | DisputeRaised | FundsReleased | etc.
  │
  ▼
NestJS EventEmitter fires event
  │
  ▼
NotificationService subscribes and determines:
  • Which users receive this notification
  • Which channels (EMAIL / SMS / IN_APP) based on user preferences
  • Which template to use (subject + body with variable injection)
  │
  ▼
Job pushed to BullMQ queue (Redis-backed)
  │  Async — does not block the original API request
  │
  ▼
BullMQ worker picks up job and dispatches:
  EMAIL  → SendGrid API
  SMS    → Twilio API (Jazz/Telenor/Ufone)
  IN_APP → WebSocket push to connected session
  │
  ▼
WRITE to [ notifications ]
  │  • status = SENT | FAILED
  │  • sent_at = timestamp of successful dispatch
  │
  ▼
On FAILED: automatic retry (3 attempts with exponential backoff)
After 3 failures: status = FAILED, admin alert triggered
```

