## 12. Table Dependency Map

This section shows the **full dependency tree** — which tables must exist before others can receive data.

### Dependency Levels

```
LEVEL 0 — No dependencies (created independently):
┌─────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                  users                       │
│  (Root table. Everything depends on this.)   │
└─────────────────────────────────────────────┘

LEVEL 1 — Depend only on users:
┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐
│   wallets    │  │kyc_documents │  │  audit_logs  │
│(user_id FK)  │  │(user_id FK)  │  │(actor_id FK) │
└──────────────┘  └──────────────┘  └──────────────┘
┌──────────────┐
│notifications │
│(user_id FK)  │
└──────────────┘

LEVEL 2 — Depend on users × 2 (client + freelancer):
┌────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│               contracts                    │
│  (client_id FK → users)                    │
│  (freelancer_id FK → users)                │
└────────────────────────────────────────────┘

LEVEL 3 — Depend on contracts (and indirectly users):
┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐
│   payments   │  │  milestones  │  │   disputes   │
│(contract_id) │  │(contract_id) │  │(contract_id) │
│(user_id)     │  │              │  │(raised_by)   │
└──────────────┘  └──────────────┘  │(assigned_to) │
                                     └──────────────┘
```

### Insertion Order (Required for FK Integrity)

```
1. users          ← must be inserted first, always
2. wallets        ← after users (one per user)
3. kyc_documents  ← after users
4. contracts      ← after users (needs client_id and freelancer_id)
5. milestones     ← after contracts
6. payments       ← after contracts and users
7. disputes       ← after contracts and users
8. audit_logs     ← after users (but written continuously alongside all others)
9. notifications  ← after users (but written continuously alongside all others)
```

